description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for individuals who are capable of providing compassionate care to patients in a busy, challenging and rewarding environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you have excellent communication skills?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can you maintain a high degree of confidentiality, work to deadlines and provide excellent personal care to our patients?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you enjoy working as part of team?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sara, one of our Care Support Workers says, “In this role no two days are the same so you will get plenty of variety. My excellent team is very supportive.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be given full training and have the opportunity to work towards the nationally recognised Care Certificate over a six-month period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Care Support Workers are expected to work a combination of days, nights and weekends including Bank Holidays and Christmas Day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Early – 07:15 to 15:15&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Late – 12:15 to 20:15hrs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Night – 19:45hrs to 07:45hrs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long Day – 07:15hrs to 20:15hrs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be conducted via video call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLesley DanbyJob title MatronTelephone number01423 553168&lt;/p&gt;
